  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In this sort of political situation, there were Jews who took advantage and became big exponents of the communist system, and others who simply didn't want to collaborate with the communists, which was the case of my father and my family.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Some members of my family became prominent members of the communist [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] party, but they can blame them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I can't blame them at all because the communists during the war were the only forces who fought against the Nazis, and for Jews, it was only one way to fight the Nazis, through the communist party.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] One of my uncles, a brother of my mother, became a member of the communist party.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He was caught by the collaborating police of Romania, was totally in touch with the Germans and so, and he was sent to jail, together with other communists.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The fact that he wasn't executed is due to, I think, the valiance of my father, who went to the place in Galatz, where the trial of this communist took place.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was a very courageous, I would say [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] unthinkable gesture, to take a train during the war from Iasi to go to Galatz and to find a lawyer for him and to pay for the lawyer.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And having a lawyer, he managed to get life in prison, something like this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But what was worse was that the rest of [non-English speech] family was arrested.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My grandmother, and together with the three daughters, who were unmarried, and they were in their late teens and were taken to [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] concentration camp, where they were subjected, these young girls, to rape for many months.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Two of them, they lost their minds.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They weren't the same, and they suffered.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
